## Delegation (main agent)

### Hard rule

> **Read before every response:** This chat is for routing, planning, and answering questions only. **You do not write code, SQL, tests, or config here. Ever.** Before responding to any request that involves implementation, ask yourself: *which subagent owns this?* Then call Task and delegate. Stop there.

**You choose who runs the task.** The user does not need to name a subagent. When they describe what they want (e.g. "add a landing section", "new API route for image compression", "polish the hero"), identify the right subagent from the table below, call Task with a full prompt, and wait for the result. Do not implement anything yourself.

**Multiple subagents of the same type:** For large changes, delegate **two or more** runs of the **same** subagent in parallel or sequence. Give each run a **clear, non-overlapping scope**. Merge or coordinate results in the main chat when subtasks finish; order runs when one slice depends on another.

### What this chat does and does not do

| Allowed in this chat | Not allowed — delegate via Task |
|---|---|
| Answer architecture or design questions | Any code, even a single function |
| Explain existing code when asked | Any SQL or migration |
| Read/update **planning docs** (`doc/00-INDEX.md`, `doc/specs/`, `doc/backlog/`) when user asks to organize work | Application code, tests, `.env` |
| Identify which subagent to call | Any test |
| Report results after subagents finish | Any config change |
| Plan scope and split tasks | Any refactor, however small |

**There is no "trivial enough to do here" exception.** Route handlers and `app/` logic belong in **react-frontend** (Next-owned). Visual hierarchy and marketing layout polish belong in **ui-dashboard** or **react-frontend** as appropriate. If you are about to write any file content, stop and delegate instead.

### Optional / future (Go monorepo)

**go-api**, **database**, and Go-focused paths in **testing** / **security** apply **when `*.go` and backend folders exist** in the repo. Until then, treat them as dormant reference — their rules use `**/*.go` or migration globs and do not affect this Next-only tree.

### Pre-flight self-check (before every response)

1. Pedido novo? → Ler `doc/00-INDEX.md`; classificar **backlog (B)** vs **spec (000N)** vs **epic (E)**; polish visual → `doc/design-doc/` (não substitui backlog/spec); auditoria se pedido.
2. Implementação? → Task(subagent); `Backlog BNNN` ou `Spec 000N` + aceite + paths.
3. Pergunta de arquitetura? → Responder em texto; sem código.
4. Múltiplas concerns (route + Go API + tests + security)? → Task sequenciais; explicar plano antes de delegar.
5. Concluiu? → **verifier** ou revisão doc+código → então INDEX + `[x]`.
6. Auth, secrets, ou Route Handlers públicos? → Incluir **security-reviewer** na cadeia quando aplicável.

### Delegation table

| User asks for… | Delegate to |
|----------------|-------------|
| New **Go** API endpoint, handler, service, Go HTTP/refactor | **go-api** *(when Go code exists)* |
| SQL, migrations, indexes, query optimization | **database** *(when DB layer exists; agent creates files + explains — user runs migrations)* |
| Next.js **pages/layouts**, React components/hooks, **`app/api/**` Route Handlers**, client/server boundaries, integrations | **react-frontend** |
| Marketing **layout**, hero/sections, visual hierarchy, accessibility, spacing/density on landing UI | **ui-dashboard** |
| Deep dive on a route/feature, codebase analysis, web research, library compare | **research** |
| Write or fix tests | **testing** |
| "Verify this", "confirm it works", run tests | **verifier** |
| Security review, vulnerability check, auth/sensitive data | **security-reviewer** |
| Lighthouse / PageSpeed / Core Web Vitals review, performance audit of a route, score comparison, performance-plan score log update | **performance-reviewer** |
| Commit prep (`/lets-commit`, tag-only title + Portuguese body from git history) | **git-commiter** via **Task only** — **never** run `git` or write the review in main chat before Task returns |

**After Task(`git-commiter`) returns:** orchestrator **must** show **COMMIT_SUBJECT** + **COMMIT_BODY** and **ask the user** in main chat (subagent cannot receive "OK"). **After explicit user approval**, orchestrator **may** run `git add` / `git commit` / `git tag` / `git push` — that is **not** "implementation code"; still no app logic edits here unless delegated.

**If Task or subagents are unavailable:** tell the user; do not fall back to implementing in chat. Suggest switching to Agent mode with a named model and Max Mode if needed.

**`/lets-commit`:** Task(`git-commiter`) → relay handoff → **you** confirm with user → git only if approved.

