## Project Structure (canonical reference)

The layout below is the **single source of truth** for where code lives in this repo.

```
/
├── doc/                         # Documentação central
│   ├── 00-INDEX.md              # Vitrine de planejamento (ler primeiro)
│   ├── design-doc/              # Design system VISUAL (cores, tipografia, componentes)
│   ├── backlog/                 # B001, B002, … — 1 arquivo por fix pequeno
│   ├── specs/                   # 0001, 0002, … — features grandes
│   ├── epics/                   # E001, … — análises longas
│   └── adr/                     # Decisões arquiteturais
├── docs/                        # Runbooks (deploy, operação) — opcional
├── app/                         # App Router: routes, layouts, pages, route groups
│   ├── api/                     # Route Handlers (e.g. Node + sharp)
│   ├── components/              # Shared UI (if present)
│   ├── globals.css              # Tailwind v4 entry (@import "tailwindcss"; @theme)
│   ├── layout.js|tsx            # Root layout
│   └── page.js|tsx              # Routes as folders with page files
├── cmd/api/                     # Go API entry (when backend exists)
├── internal/                    # handler, service, repository (when Go exists)
├── migrations/                  # SQL migrations (when DB exists)
├── public/                      # Static assets (images, icons)
├── package.json                 # next, react, tailwindcss, @tailwindcss/postcss, etc.
├── next.config.mjs
├── postcss.config.mjs           # @tailwindcss/postcss
├── AGENTS.md                    # Next.js editor notice → node_modules/next/dist/docs/
└── .cursor/                     # Rules, agents, skills (this tree)
```

- **Tailwind CSS v4:** configured via `app/globals.css` and PostCSS — **no** root `tailwind.config.*`; theme extensions use inline `@theme` where needed.
- When the repo grows (e.g. monorepo with Go), **update this section** so it stays accurate.

